Pt arrived ambulatory at 10am and stated had breakfast today. Wt-75.7kg; Ht-5'4"; BP-108/63; HRR-53; T-36.7; POX-98% on room air. Dr. Chen consented pt on protocol 20-cc-0092; Dr. Rai completed H&P in Dowling clinic. Pt given juices, refused snacks. RAC (Median) vein accessed successfully with 21G butterfly needle by HNP1, however only 25cc of draw samples and blood flow stopped. Pt prefered to get re-stick vs. needle adjustment. So needle removed and pressure dressing applied. NO infiltration and hematoma noted. 2nd attempt successful at RAC (Cephalic) vein with 21G butterfly needle by HNP1 and remaining all samples drawn. Copy of signed consent given to pt. Pt refused snacks and juices. At 12pm, pt discharged from DTM in a stable condition and with steady gait.
